◆ TexCompressionType

enum wmoge::TexCompressionType
strong

Supported types of block compression for textures.

Enumerator
Unknown 
BC1 

BC1 Mode.

Type of data: RGB + optional 1-bit alpha Data rate: 0.5 byte/px Pallet size: 4 Line segments: 1 Use for: Color maps, Cutout color maps (1-bit alpha), Normal maps, if memory is tight

BC2 

BC2 Mode.

Type of data: RGB + 4-bit alpha Data rate: 1 byte/px Pallet size: 4 Line segments: 1 Use for: n/a

BC3 

BC3 Mode.

Type of data: RGBA Data rate: 1 byte/px Pallet size: 4 color + 8 alpha Line segments: 1 color + 1 alpha Use for: Color maps with full alpha, Packing color and mono maps together

BC4 

BC4 Mode.

Type of data: Grayscale Data rate: 0.5 byte/px Pallet size: 8 Line segments: 1 Use for: Height maps, Gloss maps, Font atlases, Any grayscale image

BC5 

BC5 Mode.

Type of data: 2 grayscale Data rate: 1 byte/px Pallet size: 8 per channel Line segments: 1 per channel Use for: Tangent-space normal maps

BC6 

BC6 Mode.

Type of data: RGB, floating-point Data rate: 1 byte/px Pallet size: 816 Line segments: 12 Use for: HDR images

BC7 

BC7 Mode.

Type of data: RGB or RGBA Data rate: 1 byte/px Pallet size: 416 Line segments: 13 Use for: High-quality color maps, Color maps with full alpha
